\par \par \par \b\fs24 SETUP & DEPLOYMENT\b0\fs20
\par \par \b Prerequisites:\b0
\par - Google Account (for Sheets & Apps Script)
\par - Web hosting (GitHub Pages, Netlify, or any HTTPS server)
\par - Staff list with PIN assignments
\par \par \b Installation Steps:\b0
\par \par \b 1. Set up Google Sheets\b0
\par Create spreadsheet with three sheets:
\par - Staff (columns: Name, PIN, Active)
\par - Submissions (columns: Room, Service Type, Staff, Timestamp, Actions, Notes, Synced, ID, Device)
\par - Access Log (columns: Event, Staff, Timestamp, Details)
\par \par \b 2. Create Google Apps Script\b0
\par 1. In Sheets, go to Tools → Script Editor
\par 2. Replace default code with the backend script
\par 3. Deploy as web app (Execute as: Your account, Access: Anyone)
\par 4. Copy the deployment URL
\par 5. Replace CONFIG.SHEETS_URL in housekeeping.html with your URL
\par \par \b 3. Deploy Frontend\b0
\par 1. Save housekeeping.html to your web server
\par 2. Ensure HTTPS is enabled
\par 3. Configure staff names in Google Sheets
\par 4. Generate/hash staff PINs
\par 5. Share app URL with staff
\par \par \b 4. Testing\b0
\par 1. Log in as test staff member
\par 2. Complete full workflow (all steps to submit)
\par 3. Verify data appears in Google Sheets
\par 4. Test offline mode by disabling connection
\par 5. Verify sync resumes when connection restored
\par \par \b Configuration:\b0
\par In housekeeping.html, adjust the CONFIG object:
\par \par const CONFIG = \{
\par   SHEETS_URL: 'https://script.google.com/macros/s/YOUR_ID/exec',
\par   TIMEOUT_MINS: 20,
\par   ROOMS: ['101', '102', '103', ...]
\par \}
\par \par \b Customizable Elements:\b0
\par - Room numbers list
\par - Service types (or add more)
\par - Checklist items
\par - Action item labels
\par - Colors (CSS variables)
